parameters: \n< Serena >Excuse me, are you Lord Tomo?

\n< Monster Doctor >Is that so... Did you come to ask about the
Minotaur too?
\n< Serena >Me too?

\n< Serena >Well, it's not that I'm not interested in the
monster called Minotaur, but what I want to ask
about now is about the Orcs.

\n< Monster Doctor >So you came to learn about the enemy. That's quite
something.

\n< Monster Doctor >You adventurers are, after all, monster
exterminators. And yet, you can be said to be
quite ignorant about monsters.

\n< Monster Doctor >The fact that their extermination is not
progressing at all is probably due to that as
well.
\n< Serena >I don't intend to make such a big deal out of it.
\n< Serena >It's just for self-defense.
\n< Monster Doctor >Alright, alright.

\n< Monster Doctor >For the sake of self-defense. It's perfectly fine.
It's amazing how many people despise even the
learning necessary for that.

\n< Monster Doctor >Ignorance, you see, is no different from a slow
suicide.
\n< Monster Doctor >To live well means to learn well.
\n< Monster Doctor >Let me give you this book.
\n< Serena >...？

\n< Serena >It started. Is it some kind of magic book? How
reckless...

\n< Monster Doctor >That book... or rather, now it's yours... borrows
a little bit of your... in other words, your
magical power. It's a moving object.
\n< Monster Doctor >Open it up and take a look inside.

\n< Serena >...Goblins...Orcs...and the rest of the pages are
all blank.
\n< Serena >What is this?

\n< Monster Doctor >It's amazing how most of it is blank. That just
means you don't know about monsters.

\n< Serena >...In other words, this book is connected to my
knowledge.

\n< Monster Doctor >That's right. You're really good at smooth
talking.

\n< Serena >However, with this, it can't be considered
preparation for the unknown, can it?

\n< Serena >What I want is not a diary, but a practical book.
Practical knowledge. I do think the mechanism of
this book is interesting, but...

\n< Serena >...I apologize. I may have been a bit rude with my
words to someone I just met.

\n< Serena >By the way, I haven't introduced myself yet. I'm
Serena. Nice to meet you, Lord Tomo.
\n< Monster Doctor >Ah, it's fine, it's fine.

\n< Monster Doctor >Honest opinion. It's perfectly fine. There is no
mistake in what you say.

\n< Monster Doctor >Please think of that book as just a token of our
acquaintance.

\n< Monster Doctor >Now, about orcs. To get straight to the point,
what you want to know is their weakness, right?
Not their ecology.

\n< Serena >That's right. There's no time to listen to a long
lecture.
\n< Monster Doctor >It's fine, it's fine.

\n< Monster Doctor >Well, let's get straight to the point. We
shouldn't engage in a direct confrontation with
them.

\n< Monster Doctor >You must not try to take their attacks. It's
unbearable and you must not try to continuously
attack them. They are resilient and won't easily
back down.

\n< Monster Doctor >So, if you're going to do it, it's either
relentlessly attacking with powerful long-range
attacks or taking advantage of their openings to
strike and then retreat.

\n< Monster Doctor >Well, the orcs also know their weaknesses. That's
why they appear in groups of two or three.

\n< Monster Doctor >It's best to fight without being greedy and with
caution. Magic attacks are effective against them,
so you have an advantage.
\n< Serena >My attack method is magic?

\n< Monster Doctor >Is that not the case? With those slender arms, you
wouldn't be able to swing a sword or an axe,
right?
\n< Monster Doctor >Naturally, your attack method would be magic.
\n< Serena >I see.
\n< Monster Doctor >That's about it. Did it serve as a reference?
\n< Serena >Oh, Lord Toma.
\n< Monster Doctor >I'm the doctor.
\n< Serena >Huh?
\n< Monster Doctor >If you're going to call me, it's Monster Doctor.

\n< Monster Doctor >It's a nickname that the people in the rural town
gave me as a joke. But I actually quite like it.

\n< Serena >I understand. Monster Doctor, it was very helpful.
As a token of my gratitude...

\n< Monster Doctor >Coins are fine. It would be rather awkward for me
to charge a lecture fee for something like this.

\n< Monster Doctor >If it's a reward you're talking about, then please
keep that book I gave you safe.

\n< Serena >This is a confusing conversation. Receiving an
object as gratitude.

\n< Monster Doctor >The fact that this book exists in this world
itself will eventually become a value.

\n< Monster Doctor >Well then... if it's alright with you, please show
it to me someday.

\n< Serena >...So, is it an experiment to see what kind of
content is described?

\n< Monster Doctor >There is no significant difference in
understanding in that regard.

\n< Serena >....Well... if that's the case, I can understand
it to some extent. Okay, I got it. I'll accept it.
\n< Monster Doctor >That's good. That's good.
\n< Serena >Yes. Then, Monster Doctor, someday...

\n< Monster Doctor >You're quite an interesting individual. You have
good talent, good magical power, and a good
appearance.
\n< Monster Doctor >Truly 'good'.

\n< Monster Doctor >If even I think so, then it's probably even more
so for monsters.

\n< Monster Doctor >Her illustrated guidebook seems to be something
unprecedented.
\n< Monster Doctor >...I'm looking forward to it, Serena-kun.

\n< Monster Doctor >If you have any more questions about monsters,
feel free to come back.
\n< Serena >It's a box.
\n< Serena >It's filled with daily necessities.
\n< Serena >It's not something you see often.

\n< Serena >When I was peering into it, I made eye contact

\n< Serena >Here's a book.
\n< Serena >Monster Breeding Forms. Their Surface and Essence.

\n< Serena >Hmm... To be honest, this book has a slightly

\n< Serena >It's full of holes and unreadable, but it seems

\n< Serena >It's the stove.

\n< Serena >It doesn't feel used. It seems like she doesn't

\n< Serena >It's a pot. The lid is closed.

\n< Serena >I feel like the monster doctor is a bit
suspicious. If they come into the house and start
ignoring me to search for something, it might
become like that.
\n< Serena >It's wheat.

\n< Serena >It's placed haphazardly. I'm worried that bugs
might start crawling in with its mouth wide open.
\n< Serena >It's a fireplace.

\n< Serena >No sense of use. It seems like I just moved in
recently.
\n< Serena >It's the closet.

\n< Serena >I don't really want to see inside. As for the
exterior... well, it looks heavy. Yeah.
\n< Serena >It's the bookshelf.

\n< Serena >Here, there are books from the Seven Liberal Arts,
not just related to monsters. There seems to be a
good number of books on astronomy as well.
\n< Serena >It's a person's letter.
\n< Serena >It's not good to peek.
